{"TopicId":19321,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.3.1] Ferram Aerospace Research: v0.15.9.1 \u0026quot;Liepmann\u0026quot; 4/2/18","CreatedByName":"ferram4","CreatedById":21328,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-09-14T23:22:36Z","PageNum":496,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"OliverPA","CreatedById":164072,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-21T18:59:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSame here: TweakScale \u002B \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E = floating vessel at start and a crash soon after. Rescale to 100% = no issues\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/106366090/output_log.zip\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Elog\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ferram4","CreatedById":21328,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-21T19:06:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s the solution for the Tweakscale interaction issue: wait until 1.1.3.\u00A0 I\u0027m not going to push a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E update with that fix when 1.1.3 seems to be so close.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"the_machemer","CreatedById":140907,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-21T23:27:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIm experiencing some phantom rolling on some of my aircraft. Its nothing serious, just a very gradual roll, but Im a bit of a perfectionist and it\u00A0bothers me. Ive made sure everything was built symmetrically and with angle snap yet sometimes certain wing parts are exerting aerodynamic forces that they shouldnt be. For example, I was just flying a plane where the rudder was producing lift to the left (thus rolling the plane) even tho it was\u00A0angled straight on into the air flow. I then edited some unrelated part of the plane and it\u00A0was fixed. I did some more editing and the problem\u00A0was back again.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot exactly a super critical issue but if anyone has experienced this and knows how to prevent it, Id be grateful.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kurtvw","CreatedById":83214,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-22T01:17:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222635610\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466211801\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165595\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lasergladiatrix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/17/2016 at 6:03 PM, lasergladiatrix said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know if this is a known bug, but after I installed \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E, all my vessels start torquing counterclockwise when I turn off \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E, even in vacuum. Uninstalling \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E fixes it. Does anyone know a fix that lets me keep \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E? Thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222635827\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466230336\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258513\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gryphon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/17/2016 at 11:12 PM, Gryphon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you have any of the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E flight assists active (even in a vacuum)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222635937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466245409\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165595\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lasergladiatrix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/18/2016 at 3:23 AM, lasergladiatrix said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, I did have those enabled. Turning them off fixed the issue, thank you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/21328-ferram4/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002221328\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/21328-ferram4/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@ferram4\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/58513-gryphon/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002258513\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/58513-gryphon/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Gryphon\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI had this exact problem, and I believe it started with \u0027Knudsen\u0027. \u00A0And this solution also worked for me, so thanks for that.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIs there an intent to correct this in a future version (I hope)? \u00A0 Since \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E knows when you\u0027re not in atmosphere, it seems like it should know not to apply these corrections when you are not.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThanks for any thoughts on that. \u00A0This glitch has had me stumped for a while, but since I run a lot of mods, it took me forever to track it down to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E, and since it was happening in space, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E wasn\u0027t a mod that I suspected until I had eliminated everything else, and then Surprise!\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nLove your work Ferram. \u00A0 Keep it up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ferram4","CreatedById":21328,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-22T02:55:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/140907-the_machemer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022140907\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/140907-the_machemer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@the_machemer\u003C/a\u003E: If the rudder is producing a leftward force on the plane, then the rudder is not on straight.\u00A0 Angle snap does not always put parts directly straight, especially when they\u0027re placed on parts that don\u0027t have simple, cylindrical colliders.\u00A0 This is a long-standing issue in the stock game that will also show itself under stock aerodynamics and it is not something I can fix, nor is trying to fix part attachment issues in the editor in scope for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83214-kurtvw/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002283214\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/83214-kurtvw/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Kurtvw\u003C/a\u003E: That is not an issue.\u00A0 That is exactly how the Flight Assistants have always behaved; they remain on when you leave them on, because you told them to be turned on.\u00A0 This behavior has existed since the original \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E v0.1 and will not be removed because the game deciding \u0022no, you didn\u0027t really want this control system active, I know better than you you poor, dumb player\u0022 is the worst kind of behavior to add.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kurtvw","CreatedById":83214,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-22T03:40:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222640978\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466564141\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002221328\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ferram4\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, ferram4 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83214-kurtvw/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002283214\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/83214-kurtvw/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@Kurtvw\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0That is not an issue.\u00A0 That is exactly how the Flight Assistants have always behaved; they remain on when you leave them on, because you told them to be turned on. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/21328-ferram4/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002221328\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/21328-ferram4/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@ferram4\u003C/a\u003E, Fair enough, I never noticed it before... But perhaps you can answer another question on this same topic... That \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003EAOA\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E assist, if it is on in space, how is it determining the relative wind to get \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003EAOA\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E? \u00A0 Could an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003EAOA\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E of NaN be the source of what I saw? \u00A0(the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003EAOA\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E assist was on).\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile I agree that trying to out think the dumb user is a bad approach, I think most folks would also agree that if the input to a function is invalid or illogical, then the function should not be continuing to try to do calculations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-22T15:33:20Z\u0022 title=\u002206/22/2016 03:33  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 22, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Kurtvw\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"the_machemer","CreatedById":140907,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-22T07:59:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222640978\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466564141\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002221328\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ferram4\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, ferram4 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/140907-the_machemer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022140907\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/140907-the_machemer/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@the_machemer\u003C/a\u003E: If the rudder is producing a leftward force on the plane, then the rudder is not on straight.\u00A0 Angle snap does not always put parts directly straight, especially when they\u0027re placed on parts that don\u0027t have simple, cylindrical colliders.\u00A0 This is a long-standing issue in the stock game that will also show itself under stock aerodynamics and it is not something I can fix, nor is trying to fix part attachment issues in the editor in scope for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the info. Ive never played without \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E so i kinda assumed\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ratchet freak","CreatedById":119895,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-22T10:35:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222640978\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466564141\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002221328\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ferram4\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, ferram4 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83214-kurtvw/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002283214\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/83214-kurtvw/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@Kurtvw\u003C/a\u003E: That is not an issue.\u00A0 That is exactly how the Flight Assistants have always behaved; they remain on when you leave them on, because you told them to be turned on.\u00A0 This behavior has existed since the original \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E v0.1 and will not be removed because the game deciding \u0022no, you didn\u0027t really want this control system active, I know better than you you poor, dumb player\u0022 is the worst kind of behavior to add.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/21328-ferram4/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002221328\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/21328-ferram4/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@ferram4\u003C/a\u003E A little checkbox that says \u0022disable Flight Assist in vacuum\u0022 in the dialog would stop these little reports though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cantab","CreatedById":104935,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-22T11:57:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222640978\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466564141\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002221328\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ferram4\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, ferram4 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83214-kurtvw/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002283214\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/83214-kurtvw/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@Kurtvw\u003C/a\u003E: That is not an issue.\u00A0 That is exactly how the Flight Assistants have always behaved; they remain on when you leave them on, because you told them to be turned on.\u00A0 This behavior has existed since the original \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E v0.1 and will not be removed because the game deciding \u0022no, you didn\u0027t really want this control system active, I know better than you you poor, dumb player\u0022 is the worst kind of behavior to add.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve suggested before, some way for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E to indicate the Flight Assistant is on might be warranted though. A highlight on the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E icon, perhaps? Or how about only having it on when the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E window is open, and turning it off when that window is closed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gryphon","CreatedById":58513,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-22T17:06:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222641450\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466596631\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022104935\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cantab\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, cantab said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve suggested before, some way for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E to indicate the Flight Assistant is on might be warranted though. A highlight on the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E icon, perhaps? Or how about only having it on when the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E window is open, and turning it off when that window is closed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like your first suggestion (indicating that one or more Flight Assists are active by \u0022lighting up\u0022 the toolbar icon) but not so much your second one - you gotta be able to close the window without affecting the mod behavior.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-22T17:19:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222641944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466615186\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258513\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gryphon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, Gryphon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like your first suggestion (indicating that one or more Flight Assists are active by \u0022lighting up\u0022 the toolbar icon) but not so much your second one - you gotta be able to close the window without affecting the mod behavior.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTake a look at the way Automated Screenshots \u0026amp; Saves works. \u00A0The button icon changes color depending on what\u0027s going on\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vegetal","CreatedById":147251,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-23T06:02:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/140907-the_machemer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022140907\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/140907-the_machemer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@the_machemer\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0and \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/21328-ferram4/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002221328\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/21328-ferram4/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@ferram4\u003C/a\u003E: actually guys... ferram, remember that old voxelization problem with those pwings I reported and you solved? Well, thats the cause, except there\u0027s no need for mod parts (I sent you a stock plane that exhibited the behaviour right?). I just noticed it tonight, took a screen of the voxel debug showing the problem. Gotta go sleep now, but will post it tomorrow.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFact is, that problem never went away completely for me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ferram4","CreatedById":21328,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T02:12:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd now, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFAR\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E v0.15.7 \u003C/strong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dietrich_K%C3%BCchemann\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u0022K\u00FCchemann\u0022\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/a\u003E is out, with 1.1.3 compatibility and a few bugfixes and voxel optimizations.\u00A0 Also a fix for a possible race condition that might have been hitting some people.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ilya","CreatedById":138097,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T11:39:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222644838\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466734349\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002221328\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ferram4\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, ferram4 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd now, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E v0.15.7 \u003C/strong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dietrich_K%C3%BCchemann\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u0022K\u00FCchemann\u0022\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/a\u003E is out, with 1.1.3 compatibility and a few bugfixes and voxel optimizations.\u00A0 Also a fix for a possible race condition that might have been hitting some people.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis changelog seems great, but this version broke solar panels here. They no longer produce electricity. Reverting to the previous one fixes it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ferram4","CreatedById":21328,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T12:17:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/138097-ilya/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022138097\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/138097-ilya/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Ilya\u003C/a\u003E: I have tested all stock panels on the pad and each of them produces a electricity.\u00A0 I need full reproduction steps and a copy of the log.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ilya","CreatedById":138097,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T12:46:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222645276\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466770634\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002221328\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ferram4\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n27 minutes ago, ferram4 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/138097-ilya/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022138097\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/138097-ilya/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@Ilya\u003C/a\u003E: I have tested all stock panels on the pad and each of them produces a electricity.\u00A0 I need full reproduction steps and a copy of the log.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere aren\u0027t really reproduction steps in particular. Panels aren\u0027t working, whether it\u0027s on my already existing crafts or new ones on the launch pad, even though clicking on the panels tell me they\u0027re receiving light.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nLog:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://files.fm/u/s8ge5zw2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://files.fm/u/s8ge5zw2\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phineas Freak","CreatedById":146521,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T13:07:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/138097-ilya/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022138097\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/138097-ilya/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Ilya\u003C/a\u003Ewhat is the exact version of Kopernicus that you are using? There has been a \u0022silent\u0022 bugfix release for exactly the problem that you are facing here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ilya","CreatedById":138097,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T13:24:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222645328\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466773659\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146521\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Phineas Freak\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, Phineas Freak said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/138097-ilya/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022138097\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/138097-ilya/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@Ilya\u003C/a\u003Ewhat is the exact version of Kopernicus that you are using? There has been a \u0022silent\u0022 bugfix release for exactly the problem that you are facing here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPretty sure I was up to date, but I just downloaded the latest one anyway to test, and the problem is still there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-24T13:24:46Z\u0022 title=\u002206/24/2016 01:24  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 24, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Ilya\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cantab","CreatedById":104935,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T14:04:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222645304\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466772362\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022138097\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ilya\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Ilya said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere aren\u0027t really reproduction steps in particular.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFull reproduction steps includes details of your KSP installation, including what other mods if any you have installed. And if you can\u0027t reproduce the issue in a clean install with as few mods as possible, then it\u0027s an issue with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E interacting with some other mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ilya","CreatedById":138097,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T14:27:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, I\u0027ve isolated the problem to a compatibility issue between Kopernicus and\u00A0K\u00FCchemann (specifically). There\u0027s no doubt that those two are causing the issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"genbrien","CreatedById":131978,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T16:47:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI only got lift in campaign\u00A0and sandbox\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I play tutorials or\u00A0scenarios, I only get drag\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGot that problem with 15.6 and 15.7\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand with ksp 1.1.2/ 1.1.3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: seems that if I start the game, then load a tutorial or a scenario, I got no lift.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBUT, if I load a campagn, or a sandbox, and then start a tutorial or scenario I\u0027ll get lift\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-24T16:55:36Z\u0022 title=\u002206/24/2016 04:55  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 24, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by genbrien\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kcs123","CreatedById":127158,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T16:55:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222645624\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466786834\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022131978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022genbrien\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, genbrien said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI only got lift in campaign\u00A0and sandbox\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I play tutorials or\u00A0scenarios, I only get drag\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGot that problem with 15.6 and 15.7\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand with ksp 1.1.2/ 1.1.3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you install any mod, it can break tutorials. Tutorials are kind of special when comes to moding.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf you want to go trough tutorials you should do that without any mod installed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat was known issue for all previous versions of KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wedgenet","CreatedById":72682,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T17:35:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222645432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466778452\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022138097\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ilya\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Ilya said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, I\u0027ve isolated the problem to a compatibility issue between Kopernicus and\u00A0K\u00FCchemann (specifically). There\u0027s no doubt that those two are causing the issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/138097-ilya/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022138097\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/138097-ilya/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Ilya\u003C/a\u003E I experience this bug now and I am still running the previous version of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E: v0.15.6.5 \u0022Knudsen\u0022, so I don\u0027t believe that it is new to K\u00FCchemann, or even necessarily related to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-24T17:36:23Z\u0022 title=\u002206/24/2016 05:36  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 24, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Wedgenet\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E@\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ilya","CreatedById":138097,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T17:37:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222645664\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466789747\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002272682\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wedgenet\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Wedgenet said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI experience this bug now and I am still running the previous version of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E: v0.15.6.5 \u0022Knudsen\u0022, so I don\u0027t believe that it is new to K\u00FCchemann, or even necessarily related to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aeronautics Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI found the real issue thanks to the Kopernicus thread. It\u0027s actually Modular Flight Integrator. It seems that kuchermann came with an old version of it that still had the bug. Just go in the MFI thread and download the newest one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vegetal","CreatedById":147251,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T23:23:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222645667\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002219321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466789873\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022138097\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ilya\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Ilya said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI found the real issue thanks to the Kopernicus thread. It\u0027s actually Modular Flight Integrator. It seems that kuchermann came with an old version of it that still had the bug. Just go in the MFI thread and download the newest one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSolution confirmed. I was having the same issue, gone now. Thanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}